snippet.textDisplay: So the first time I got really high I had 4 or 5 beers before hand too. I wanted the high to stop once I kept getting higher as time went on and fell into extreme paranoia to the point of hallucinating. I happened to be at a Rugby party  at the University of Miami and we partied hard haha. The music was loud and the Rugby house was packed with people. I ended up hearing this loud laugh after I noticed people noticing how paranoid I was getting. I took off out the house barefoot and with a badly hurt collar bone from the days Rugby match(that I couldn't feel at all). I could only run on the white lines of the road and didn't see cars until running for what seemed a minute and felt out of control of my body the whole time. I wasn't even tired. My friends ended catching me and brought me back to the house. This happened 3 more times, but I felt like I did it way more than that due to my weird time distortion I was having. Literally thought I was in hell for 12 straight hours that night. This little video is described my onset of paranoia minus the suicide the committed. Can't tell you the level of fear I felt thinking I was in hell.
